Sansa is never wrong and they defend and excuse everything that they take others to task for. I’m not even a Dany Stan and was surprised by sansa’s behavior. Dany is supposed to show Sansa respect and not react to disrespect, but Sansa is “right” for mean mugging Dany and being snarky because her past???

Sansa’s a “queen”, but can’t conduct herself as such when encountering a situation she doesn’t like? But, Dany saying one remark and complaining to Jon in private proves she mad and isn’t fit to be queen.

Y’all wild.

title: No.
body:
You know, I’m the first in line to throw stones at Jon for how he “didn’t care” about the arsonist iguana threatening Sansa in 8x1, even if I 100% believe he’s just playing a part. I’m actually quite ride or die about this, he’s either faking his arse with that tyranical lizard or Arya can choke him.

Now, putting up airs that “Robb would never?”

Robb left Sansa and Arya in King’s Landing to be beaten every day, to be threatened with death and rape every day. He left them there because he didn’t want to bend the knee to the Lannisters nor did he want to trade Jaime Lannister for the girls, because he couldn’t risk his war for ReVeNgE and northern independence. Then risked his war so he could shack up to some chick he met for two weeks.

That’s fine, you know? Robb can set up his priorities all he wants. Now saying “Robb would never”? Spare me this nonsense.

summary: I'm hoping Cersei kidnaps Sansa ASAP. Let Bran, Arya, Sam, Davos, Dany, Tormond, Edd, etc comfort him post reveal. Jon got a...
question: I'm hoping Cersei kidnaps Sansa ASAP. Let Bran, Arya, Sam, Davos, Dany, Tormond, Edd, etc comfort him post reveal. Jon got a whole squad of supporters. The moment Sansa tries to help him he'd probably snap and accuse her of something. Anyways, onto something better. Richard Madden told Elle magazine, [He does, however, have a Season 8 prediction with regard to Turner’s character, Sansa Stark. “People thought she was weak and wilty,” he says, “but she’s our mother’s daughter, you know....”] Aww.
answer:
I love Cersei and I want to see her with Sansa but Cersei is a shit human being who will try to hurt Sansa in any way that she can. That’s why I hate the kidnapping plot. I’d rather Sansa goes to Cersei out of necessity than anything else forcing them to be on equal ground but I’m with you with the whole comforting Jon thing. I know if Sansa doesn’t, people will call her a bully or abuser or whatever but at the same time, it’s tiring seeing her always comforting Jon and getting nothing in return.

People have really been drinking the respect Sansa juice this week. I’m glad someone acknowledged that Sansa is Catelyn’s daughter

summary: Request for six sentence:  SanSan - Snowstorm
question: Request for six sentence:  SanSan - Snowstorm
answer:
“It seems that there is a snowstorm and we’re trapped Little Bird, hope it passes soon.”

“Oh? So you’re not happy to be trapped with your girlfriend for another day?” Sansa teased.

Sandor blinked, “That’s not it, I’m just worried about how the roads are going to be hell.”

Sansa went and hugged, “Relax Sandor, I grew up in this sort of weather and let me tell you, yes the roads will not be the best, but today, right in this moment, all is well.”

“I suppose you are right,” Sandor sighed, “We still have food, the phones are working, we have electricity and there is fire for the chimney.”

“See, all is well.”

***
